grady@netcom.com (1016/2EF221) writes:
> To censor distribution of ideas based upon policing other's intentions is
> morally wrong to me.  That is one reason why I support widely available
> encryption tools in the first place.

Note that there is a world of difference between "censoring" (which
noone on this thread has advocated) and pointing out that someone
might consider asking themselves a question before expending energy
to "help". You and I and everyone have a right to speak freely; we
do not have an obligation to speak, and some of us may appreciate
being reminded that there are situations where it is best not to speak.

Rob

